36.6 Chain, Sberbank, Severstal May Move: Russia Equity Preview

-- B y   H e n r y   M e y e r
-- 
2011-07-06T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/36-6-chain-sberbank-severstal-may-move-russia-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slid 0.3 percent to 1,705.41.  OAO Pharmacy Chain 36.6 (APTK RX):  Russia ’s largest drugs
retailer may report first quarter IFRS results today. The shares
lost 0.6 percent to 89.37 rubles.  OAO Sberbank (SBER03 RX): Oesterreichische Volksbanken AG
may sell its eastern European unit for at least 700 million
euros ($1 billion) to Sberbank in a deal set to be signed in
July, said two people with direct knowledge of the deal. Shares
in Russia’s largest lender rose 0.2 percent to 104.4 rubles.  OAO Severstal (CHMF RX): Russia’s largest steelmaker hired
Barclays Plc and Goldman Sachs Group Inc. to organize meetings
with investors for a possible Eurobond sale this month, Interfax
reported, citing an unidentified banker. Shares fell 0.5 percent
to 516.9 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henry Meyer in Moscow at 
